***Recipe:

churn_rec <- churn_train %>%
  recipe(formula = Churn ~.) %>%
  update_role(customerID, new_role = "id") %>%
  step_nzv(all_numeric_predictors()) %>%
  step_impute_median(all_numeric_predictors()) %>%
  step_impute_mode(all_nominal_predictors()) %>%
  step_normalize(all_numeric_predictors()) %>%
  step_other(all_nominal_predictors(),threshold = 0.05 ) %>%
  step_corr(all_numeric_predictors(),threshold = 0.9) %>%
  step_dummy(all_nominal_predictors())

# Compute AUC for all models
auc_data <- tibble(
  Model = c("Logistic Regression", "KNN", "SVM", "Bagging", "Random Forest", "Boosting"),
  AUC = c(
    churn_fit1 %>% collect_predictions() %>% roc_auc(truth = Churn, .pred_No) %>% pull(.estimate),
    churn_fit2 %>% collect_predictions() %>% roc_auc(truth = Churn, .pred_No) %>% pull(.estimate),
    churn_fit3 %>% collect_predictions() %>% roc_auc(truth = Churn, .pred_No) %>% pull(.estimate),
    churn_fit41 %>% collect_predictions() %>% roc_auc(truth = Churn, .pred_No) %>% pull(.estimate),
    churn_fit42 %>% collect_predictions() %>% roc_auc(truth = Churn, .pred_No) %>% pull(.estimate),
    churn_fit43 %>% collect_predictions() %>% roc_auc(truth = Churn, .pred_No) %>% pull(.estimate)
  )
)

# Create a simple bar plot for AUC comparison

  geom_col(width = 0.6, show.legend = FALSE) +
  labs(
